content.problemStatement:
Which of the following code snippets correctly demonstrates the scope of a loop variable declared inside a `for` loop in C++?

**A.**
```cpp
int main() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        cout << i << endl;
    }
    cout << i; 
    return 0;
}
```

**B.**
```cpp
int main() {
    int i;
    for (i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        cout << i << endl;
    }
    cout << i; 
    return 0;
}
```

**C.**
```cpp
int main() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        cout << i << endl;
    }
    int i = 10;
    cout << i;
    return 0;
}
```

**D.**
```cpp
int main() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        cout << i << endl;
    }
    cout << i + 1;
    return 0;
}
```

